Sri Lanka cricket captain
 Tillakaratne Dilshan  has been ruled out of the third Test
against  England  because of a broken thumb,  Sky Sports  reported.  The match in Southampton, southern England, starts in two
days. England holds a 1-0 lead in the three-match series.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
